      {
        "title": "Berserker",
        "excerpt": "A strong melee dude, who likes being strong and fighting in melee. The dude part is optional, and doesn’t signify gender or anything. Strong melee dudes are often found punching things or hitting things, especially when those things are enemies or are getting in the way.     Powers          Name     Tier     Type     Description                                                                                                                                              Brutish Shove                  Novice                                                                                                             Mountain Stance                  Novice                                                                                                             Power Attack                  Novice                                                                                                             Rage                  Novice                                                              You enter a furious rage, gaining offensive power at the cost of defense                                               Sudden Charge                  Novice                                                                                                             Swipe                  Novice                                                                                                             Cleave                  Veteran                                                                                                             Come and Get Me                  Veteran                                                                                                             Furious Focus                  Veteran                                                                                     Giant's Stature                  Veteran                                                                                                             Awesome Blow                  Master                                                                                                             Vengeful Strike                  Master                                                                                                             Savage Critical                  Epic                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 Brutish Shove                              Novice                                             Trigger           You hit a creature with a Strike with a two-handed melee weapon                    Requirements           The creature is your size or smaller                                  Throwing your weight behind your attack, you hit your opponent hard enough to make them stumble back. You can automatically apply the effects of the Shove action (including the critical success effect, if your Strike was a critical hit). If you move to follow the target, your movement doesn’t trigger reactions.                                  Mountain Stance                              Novice                                       Stance                                                      Requirements           You are unarmored and touching the ground                                  You end the stance of an implacable mountain and strike with the weight of an avalanche. The only Strikes you can make are falling stone unarmed attacks. These deal 1d8 bludgeoning damage and have the forceful and unarmed traits.   While in Mountain Stance, you gain a +2 bonus to Toughness, but you take a -2 penalty to Agility.                                  Power Attack                              Novice                        You unleash a particularly powerful attack that clobbers your foe but leaves you a bit unsteady. Make a melee Strike at -5 to the attack roll. If this Strike hits, you deal an extra die of weapon damage.                                  Rage                              Novice                                       Emotion                    Encounter                    Mental                                                      Duration           1 minute, until you can’t sense any enemies, or until you fall unconscious                                  You tap into your inner fury and begin raging. You gain temporary HP equal to Berserker Level + Constitution. While raging, you gain the following benefits:     You deal 2 additional damage with melee or thrown weapon Strikes. This additional damage is halved if your weapon or unarmed attack is agile.   You take a -2 penalty to Agility   You can’t use Concentrate powers                                  Sudden Charge                              Novice                                       Flourish                    Open                                 With a quick sprint, you dash up to your foe and swing. Stride twice. If you end your movement within reach of at least one enemy, you can make a melee Strike against that enemy.                                  Swipe                              Novice                                       Flourish                                 You make a wide, arcing swing. Make a single melee Strike and compare the attack roll result to the ACs of up to two foes, each of whom must be within your melee reach and adjacent to the other. Roll damage only once and apply it to each creature you hit. A Swipe counts a two attacks for MAP. If you’re using a weapon with the sweep trait, its modifier applies to all your Swipe attacks.                                  Cleave                              Veteran                                             Trigger           Your melee Strike reduces a creature to 0 HP, and another foe is adjacent to that creature                                  You swing clear through one foe and into another. Make a melee Strike against the second foe.                                  Come and Get Me                              Veteran                                             Prerequisites           Rage                    Requirements           You are raging                                  You open yourself to attacks so you can respond in turn. Until your rage ends, you are flat-footed, and damage rolls against you gain a +2 bonus. If a creature hits you, that creature is flat-footed to you until the end of your next turn. If you hit it before the end of your next turn, you gain temporary HP equal to your Constitution, or double that on a critical hit, which last until the end of your rage.                                  Furious Focus              Veteran                                             Prerequisites           Power Attack                                  You’ve learned to maintain your balance even when swinging furiously. When you make a Power Attack with a melee weapon you’re wielding in two hands, you only take a -2 penalty to the attack roll instead of -5.                                  Giant's Stature                              Veteran                                       Polymorph                                                      Prerequisites           Rage                    Requirements           You are raging, and you are Medium size or smaller                                  You grow to incredible size. You become Large, increasing your reach by 5 feet and taking a -1 penalty to Agility until you stop raging. Your equipment grows with you.                                  Awesome Blow                              Master                                             Requirements           Your last action was a successful Strike                                  The weight of your swing drives your enemy back. Attempt an Athletics roll against your target’s Fortitude save.                                   Critical Success           You gain the critical success effect of a Shove, then the critical success effect of a Trip against the target                             Success           You gain the success effect of a Shove, then the success effect of a Trip against the target                             Failure           You gain the success effect of a Shove against the target                                                        Vengeful Strike                              Master                                             Prerequisites           Come and Get Me                    Trigger           A creature within your reach succeeds or critically succeeds at an attack against you                    Requirements           You’re under the effect of Come and Get Me                                  When struck by an enemy, you respond in turn. Make a melee Strike against the triggering creature. This Strike doesn’t count toward MAP, and MAP doesn’t apply to this Strike.                                  Savage Critical              Epic                        The wounds you inflict are greivous. When you Strike, you critically succeed if you roll a 19 on the die as long as that result is a success.",
        "url": "/berserker.html"
      }
      
