      {
        "title": "Acrobat",
        "excerpt": "Powers          Name     Tier     Type     Description                                      Crane Stance                  Novice                                                                                                             Fantastic Leap                  Novice                                                                                                             Flurry of Blows                  Novice                                                                                                             Incredible Movement                  Novice                                                                                     Reactive Pursuit                  Novice                                                                                                             Stunning Fist                  Novice                                                                                                             Agile Grace                  Veteran                                                                                     Sleeper Hold                  Veteran                                                                                                             Wall Run                  Veteran                                                                                                             Water Step                  Veteran                                                                                     Whirlwind Strike                  Master                                                                                                             Enduring Quickness                  Epic                                                                                     Swift River                  Epic                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Crane Stance                              Novice                                       Stance                                                      Requirements           You are unarmored                                  You enter the stance of a crane, using flowing defensive motions. You gain a +1 bonus to AC, but the only Strike you can make is crane wing attacks. These deal 1d6 bludgeoning damage, and have the agile, finesse, and unarmed traits.   While in Crane Stance, you gain a +5 bonus to die rolls made to jump.                                  Fantastic Leap                              Novice                        You launch yourself through the air at a foe. Make a Stride by jumping. At the end of your jump, you can make a melee Strike, even if you’re in mid-air. You fall to the ground after the Strike. If the distance of your fall is no more than the height of your jump, you take no damage and land upright.                                  Flurry of Blows                              Novice                                       Flourish                                 Make two melee Strikes. If both hit the same creature, combine their damage for the purpose of resistances and weaknesses. Apply your MAP to the Strikes normally.                                  Incredible Movement              Novice                        You move like the wind. Whenever you’re not wearing armor, you gain a bonus to your Speed equal to 5 feet * your Acrobat level.                                  Reactive Pursuit                              Novice                                             Trigger           An adjacent foe moves away from you, and you can reach at least one space adjacent to the foe with a Stride action                                  You keep pace with a retreating foe. You Stride, but you must end your movement adjacent to the triggering enemy. Your move does not trigger reactions from the triggering enemy.                                  Stunning Fist                              Novice                                       Incapacitation                                                      Prerequisites           Flurry of Blows                    Trigger           You target the same creature with two Strikes from your Flurry of Blows, and at least one of the Strikes hits and deals damage.                                  The focused power of your flurry threatens to overwhelm your opponent. Your target must succeed at a Fortitude save against a DC of 10 + Strength + Prof of be stunned 1 (or stunned 3 on a critical failure).                                  Agile Grace              Veteran                        Your graceful moves with agile weapons are beyond compare. Your multiple attack penalty with agile weapons becomes -3 for each Attack power you’ve used so far this turn (rather than -4).                                  Sleeper Hold                              Veteran                                       Attack                    Incapacitation                                                      Requirements           You have a creature grabbed or restrained                                  You pinch crucial points of your target’s nervous system, impeding its ability to function. Attempt to Grapple the creature, with the following success and critical success effects instead of the usual effects.                                   Critical Success           The target falls unconscious for 1 minute, though it remains standing and doesn’t drop what it holds                             Success           The target takes a -1 penalty to Agility until the end of its next turn                                                                 Wall Run                              Veteran                        You defy gravity, traversing vertical planes as easily as the ground. Stride up to your Speed. You must start your movement on a horizontal surface. During this movement, you can run up vertical surfaces, like walls, at your full Speed. If you end the Stride off the ground, you fall after taking your next action or when your turn ends, whichever comes first. If you have Water Step or a similar ability, Wall Run lets you run along flimsy vertical surfaces, as well as vertical liquids, such as a waterfall.                                  Water Step              Veteran                        You can Stride across liquid and surfaces that don’t support your weight. This benefit only lasts during your movement. If you end your movement on a surface that can’t support you, you fall in or it collapses as normal.                                  Whirlwind Strike                              Master                                       Flourish                    Open                                 You attack all nearby adversaries. Make a melee Strike against each enemy within your melee reach. Each attack counts towards your MAP, but do not increase your penalty until you have made all your attacks.                                  Enduring Quickness              Epic                        You move as fast and as high as the wind itself. You’re permanently quickened. You can use your extra action only to Stride.                                  Swift River                              Epic                                             Trigger           Your turn ends and you have a penalty to your Speed or are immobilized or slowed                                  You flow like water, avoiding all restraints. End one penalty to your Speed, or end one immobilized or slowed condition affecting you.",
        "url": "/acrobat.html"
      }
      
        ,
      
    
  
    
      

      {
        "title": "Hunter",
        "excerpt": "Powers          Name     Tier     Type     Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      Far Shot                  Novice                                                                                     Hunt Prey                  Novice                                                                                                             Hunter's Aim                  Novice                                                                                                             Camouflage                  Veteran                                                                                     Deadly Aim                  Veteran                                                                                                             Debilitating Shot                  Veteran                                                                                                             Incredible Ricochet                  Veteran                                                                                                             Double Prey                  Master                                                                                     Legendary Shot                  Epic                                                                                     Shadow Hunter                  Epic                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Far Shot              Novice                        Your experience in the field has taught you how to focus your aim at a distance, increasing your accuracy. Double your weapons’ range increments.                                  Hunt Prey                              Novice                                       Concentrate                                                      Duration           24 hours, or until you use this power again                                  You designate a single creature as your prey and focus your attacks against that creature. You must be able to see or hear the prey, or you must be tracking the prey during exploration. You gain a +2 bonus to Perception rolls or Survival rolls made to Seek or Track your prey. You also ignore the penalty for making ranged attacks within your second increment against the prey you’re hunting. The first time you hit your hunted prey in a round, you also deal 1d8 additional precision damage.                                  Hunter's Aim                              Novice                                       Concentrate                                 By spending a moment to focus, you can ensure your attack strikes true. Make a ranged weapon Strike. On this Strike, you gain a +2 bonus to the attack roll and ignore the target’s concealed condition.                                  Camouflage              Veteran                        You alter your appearance to blend in to your surroundings. While outdoors, you can Sneak even if you’re observed.                                  Deadly Aim                              Veteran                                       Open                                 You aim for your prey’s weak spots, making your shot more challenging but dealing more damage if you hit. Make a ranged Strike against your hunted prey at a -2 penalty. Your Strike’s damage increases by 2 + Prof.                                  Debilitating Shot                              Veteran                                       Flourish                                 Aiming for a weak point, you impede your foe with a precise shot. Make a ranged weapon Strike. If it hits and deals damage, the target is slowed 1 until the end of its next turn.                                  Incredible Ricochet                              Veteran                                       Concentrate                    Press                                 After your first shot singles out your opponent’s position, you direct another that ricochets around obstacles and strikes unerringly. Make a ranged weapon Strike. You ignore the target’s concealed condition and all cover.                                  Double Prey              Master                                             Prerequisites           Hunt Prey                                  You can focus on two foes at once, hunting both of them down. When you use the Hunt Prey power, you can pick two creatures as your prey.                                  Legendary Shot              Epic                                             Prerequisites           Far Shot, Hunt Prey                                  Your focus on your hunted prey, perceiving angles, air resistance, and every variable that would affect your ranged attack. You can ignore the penalty for attacking up to five range increments away when attacking your hunted prey.                                  Shadow Hunter              Epic                                             Prerequisites           Camouflage                                  You blend in to your surroundings so well that others have trouble telling you apart from the terrain. While outdoors, you’re always concealed from all foes if you choose to be.",
        "url": "/hunter.html"
      }
      
